What's New entry files
======================

Each user-facing change gets its own file here. Different PRs add different
files, so parallel branches never conflict on the same list.

Format
------
Filename: NNNN_slug.py  (zero-padded 4-digit id, e.g. 0016_my_feature.py)
Content: a single top-level ENTRY variable:

    from metatv.whats_new import WhatsNewEntry

    ENTRY = WhatsNewEntry(
        id=16,
        version="0.8.0",
        date="2026-06-22",
        title="My feature",
        items=(
            "First bullet point.",
            "Second bullet point.",
        ),
    )

test_steps (default — include them)
-----------------------------------
Every entry for a user-visible change (feature OR bug-fix) carries a non-empty
``test_steps=(...)`` after ``items`` — the smoke test the tester/user steps
through in the dev QA checklist.  Each step is one concise string: one action +
the expected outcome, together covering the changed path end-to-end so there is
always a concrete set of tasks to verify the change.  Example:

    test_steps=(
        "Open the Recipe chip → add a Genre tag → 'Now Plating' strip populates with matching cards.",
        "Click the tag again → it toggles to ⊘ excluded → result count drops.",
    ),

Leave ``test_steps`` off (``test_steps=()`` / field absent) ONLY when there is
nothing to test by hand — a pure internal refactor with no behavior change, or
dev-only tooling like the checklist window itself; note why in the PR.  The
dev-only Testing Checklist floating window (gated by METATV_DEV env var) reads
these steps and shows them only for entries that have at least one step and
whose id exceeds the ``qa_verified_id`` config cursor.

Rules
-----
- id must be the next integer after the current maximum (run `python -c
  "from metatv.whats_new import latest_id; print(latest_id() + 1)"` to
  confirm).
- Never edit an existing entry file — changelog entries are immutable.
- Never append to a shared list — just add the new file.
- The loader sorts by id, so file discovery order and merge order do not
  matter.
